      <body>
        <div>
            <pb facs="#TL-0546.jpg" n="part4_p072.jpg" xml:id="img_0072" corresp="https://id.acdh.oeaw.ac.at/tillich-lectures/part4_p072.jpg"/>
            
            <p facs="#facs_72_tr_2">
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_2_tl_1" n="N001"/>-541.
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_2_tl_2" n="N002"/>can be identified with a law which in itself is absolute. It is even earlier to apply this to the problem
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_2_tl_3" n="N003"/>of freedom, where the question is always not only "freedom from what?" but also "freedom FOR
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_2_tl_4" n="N004"/>what?" and then a very large amount of possible answers are given.
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_2_tl_5" n="N005"/>The middle principles are matters of wisdom. They are matters of human experience
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_2_tl_6" n="N006"/>and they are product of abringing situation. Now let's say we adhere to one of these middle
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_2_tl_7" n="N007"/>axioms, or to these questions of wisdom, and come to a very concrete situation-not "very," it is
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_2_tl_8" n="N008"/>not a very good word, but "absolutely" concrete situation to the here and now. THERE AGAIN
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_2_tl_9" n="N009"/>we are in the alternative: do we apply, in the relationship to another being, an abstract law, which
            </p>
            <p facs="#facs_72_tr_3">
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_3_tl_1" n="N001"/>is certainly a matter of wisdom but not necessarily the only possible expression of love? Or do we
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_3_tl_2" n="N002"/>LISTEN to the concrete situation and try to arrive from this situation a hint to what love demands in
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_3_tl_3" n="N003"/>this moment? We shouldn’t do this arbitrarily—CERTAINLy not. But we should do it always
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_3_tl_4" n="N004"/>IN CONSIDERATION of the wisdom of mankind, because this wisdom has experience that
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_3_tl_5" n="N005"/>TRESPASSING of the laws can mean self-destruction, and destruction of others.
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_3_tl_6" n="N006"/>But there is ALS0 the principle of love, which in all periods of history has shown that spassing
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_3_tl_7" n="N007"/>of a given law is a way in which LoVE is actualized. Jesus, in his fight with the Pharisees and
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_3_tl_8" n="N008"/>their laws, continually deals with  such problems.
            </p>
            <p facs="#facs_72_tr_1">
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_1_tl_1" n="N001"/>Now I think this is the great realm of the CONTENTS of the law. Here I want to show
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_1_tl_2" n="N002"/>what is the subject matter of this lecture anyhow, namely that automomous morale need a death¬
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_1_tl_3" n="N003"/>something ultimate which gives the content and at the same
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_1_tl_4" n="N004"/>dimension, theDenension of
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_1_tl_5" n="N005"/>time liberates from every law which identifies the conconditional demand with a special law.
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_1_tl_6" n="N006"/>What we really have done here was an attempt where I leave it to your thought, and your
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_1_tl_7" n="N007"/>experience even more whether this is a way of lvercoming the destructive
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_1_tl_8" n="N008"/>conflict between moral absolutism which identifies the ultimate with a table of laws, on the one
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_1_tl_9" n="N009"/>hand; and moral relativism which makes everything depend on the cultural contents.
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_1_tl_10" n="N010"/>dʼune manière
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_1_tl_11" n="N011"/>pour entendre
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_1_tl_12" n="N012"/>sont aussi les
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_1_tl_13" n="N013"/>cʼest en
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_1_tl_14" n="N014"/>dʼun autre
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_1_tl_15" n="N015"/>pour lʼéviter
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_1_tl_16" n="N016"/>dʼOndine
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_1_tl_17" n="N017"/>cʼest lʼautre vieusement beaucoup
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_1_tl_18" n="N018"/>Monsieur Mounard, car cette
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_1_tl_19" n="N019"/>cʼest la fois
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_1_tl_20" n="N020"/>dans le
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_1_tl_21" n="N021"/>dʼun autre
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_1_tl_22" n="N022"/>dʼune manière beaucoup devenu aussi
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_1_tl_23" n="N023"/>dans le
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_1_tl_24" n="N024"/>dʼune manière beaucoup
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_1_tl_25" n="N025"/>Vous avez
               <lb facs="#facs_72_tr_1_tl_26" n="N026"/>G.C.F.P
            </p>
            
